The Dao that can be spoken is not the Dao. 
The name that can be named is not a name. 
Namelessness is the beginning of creation. 
Naming is the mother of all things. 
Absent desire, you discover wonder;
with desire, you encounter the boundaries./n/nThere are these two:
that separate from the name,
and that spoken from the darkness.

Darkness from darkness,
the gateway to myriad wonders.
